'''Gallery Galschiøt''' is a workshop in [[Odense]], [[Denmark]], and is 8,000 square meters.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.gallerigalschiot.dk/index_en.html|title = Gallery Galschiøt's webpage|date = |accessdate = |website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> Gallery Galschiøt contains the artist [[Jens Galschiot]]'s workshop.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://aidoh.dk/?categoryID=3|title = The gallery's brochure|date = |accessdate = |website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web| url=http://bøgebjergstrand.dk/side11218.html?aktid=653 |title=Gallery Galschiøt in Odense |date= |accessdate=12 June 2015 | website= |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>
In the gallery there is access to:
* The Gallery, where a large amount of Galschiot's work is exhibited.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.aidoh.dk/new-struct/Gallery-Galschiot/Visit-gallery.pdf |title = Brochure about the Gallery|date = |accessdate = |website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> Also other artists exhibits with a number of paintings etc. The gallery has also been visited by the Danish [[princess Marie of Denmark|princess Marie]]. * The workshop, where Galschiot creates his sculptures.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.visitodense.com/ln-int/danmark/gallery-galschiot-gdk691449 |title = Visit Odense's page about the gallery|date = |accessdate = |website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> * The park, where it is possible to see a lot of Galschiot's biggest [[sculptures]]. The Gallery has a permanent exhibition, which also contains works of [[Michael Kvium]], [[Jørgen Boberg]], [[Laurits Tuxen]], [[Wilhelm Marstrand]], [[Gerhard Henning]].<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.tripadvisor.com/Attraction_Review-g189524-d5016318-Reviews-Gallery_Galschioet-Odense_Funen_and_Islands.html |title=Gallery Galschioet |date = |accessdate=12 June 2015 | website=[[TripAdvisor]] |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>
==History== The buildings was originally a factory, but the artist Galschiot bought the buildings in 1994 and started transforming it into a [[workshop]].{{fact|date=June 2015}} All of the buildings have now been transformed, and most of the buildings are open to public.
Besides Gallery Galschiøt, the place also contains a [[sculpture park]], a [[television production]] company, an [[art school]] and an [[arrow]] weave [[workshop]].{{fact|date=June 2015}}
