Finnish composer [[Einojuhani Rautavaara]] wrote his '''Symphony No. 3''' in 1959-60. Although employing serial procedures, the harmonies are firmly tonal throughout. In fact, the romantic gestures of the symphony, the majestic use of brass (including [[Wagner Tuba]]s), as well as the use of German tempo markings, owes much to the symphonies of [[Anton Bruckner]], and the symphony has been termed by critics as ''neo-Brucknerian'' in style.
==Movements== #Langsam, breit, ruhig #Langsam, doch nicht schleppend #Sehr schnell #Bewegt
